'''Brückner Glacier''' ({{Coord|67|18|S|67|0|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] flowing northeast on [[Arrowsmith Peninsula]] to [[Muller Ice Shelf]] in the southwest part of [[Lallemand Fjord]], [[Loubet Coast]]. It was mapped by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] from surveys and air photos, 1956–59, and named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] after [[Eduard Brückner]], German pioneer glaciologist.

