{{short description|A galaxy that is in between the classifications of a barred spiral galaxy and an unbarred spiral galaxy}} {{Refimprove|date=December 2006}}
[[File:M83 - Southern Pinwheel.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Messier 83]] is an intermediate spiral galaxy of type SABc located in the [[constellation]] [[Hydra (constellation)|Hydra]].]]
An '''intermediate spiral galaxy''' is a [[Galaxy|galaxy]] that is in between the classifications of a [[barred spiral galaxy]] and an [[unbarred spiral galaxy]]. It is designated as '''SAB''' in the [[galaxy morphological classification]] system devised by [[Gerard de Vaucouleurs]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=de Vaucouleurs|first1=Gerard|title=Revised Classification of 1500 Bright Galaxies|journal=Astrophysical Journal Supplement|date=1963|volume=8|page=31|doi=10.1086/190084|bibcode=1963ApJS....8...31D}}</ref> Subtypes are labeled as SAB0, SABa, SABb, or SABc, following a sequence analogous to the [[Hubble sequence]] for barred and unbarred spirals. The subtype (0, a, b, or c) is based on the relative prominence of the central [[Bulge (astronomy)|bulge]] and how tightly wound the [[spiral arms]] are.
[[File:Hubble - de Vaucouleurs Galaxy Morphology Diagram.png|thumb|600px|Diagram of the Hubble - de Vaucouleurs morphological classification system illustrating the class of intermediate spirals.]]
