{{Infobox Magazine | title = Science Illustrated | image_file = Science Illustrated January February 2009 cover.jpg | image_size = 222px | image_caption = January–February 2008 issue | company = [[Bonnier Publications International]] | circulation = 370'000 | frequency = Finland, Sweden, Norway and Denmark; in every 3rd week, Iceland; 14 issues per year, Latvia, Greece, Netherlands and Lithuania; 12 issues per year, Germany; 6 issues per year | language = | category = [[Popular science]] | editor = Sebastian Relster | firstdate = {{start date and age|1984}} | website = [http://www.scienceillustrated.com/ Science Illustrated] (''English'') | issn = 0903-5583 }} '''''Science Illustrated''''' is a multilingual [[popular science]] magazine published by [[Bonnier Group|Bonnier]] Publications International A/S.<ref>{{cite news|last=Jackson|first=Sally|title=Magazine legends in their own launch time|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/media/legends-in-their-launch-time/story-e6frg996-1225700220945|newspaper=The Australian|date=20 April 2009}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''Science Illustrated'' was launched simultaneously in Denmark, Norway and Sweden in 1984.<ref>{{cite web|author=Aashild Erlandsen|title=Norway|url=http://www.cirst.uqam.ca/pcst3/PDF/actes/05-9_norway.pdf|publisher=Cirst|accessdate=14 November 2014|format=Book chapter}}</ref><ref name=bonp>{{cite web|title=Company History|url=http://en.bonnierpublications.com/company-history|publisher=Bonnier Publications|accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref> The Finnish version was started in [[Finland]] in 1986.<ref name=bonp/>
According to official websites, the magazine – with a total circulation of 370,000 copies – is the biggest in the [[Nordic countries]] with a focus on nature, technology, medicine and culture.
